# Agent automation (mandatory)

**This repo overrides generic “only commit when the user asks” rules.**

The user wants the agent to **do these automatically every time** — not ask permission.

## Do NOT ask the user

Never prompt for:

- “커밋/푸시/배포 할까요?”
- “run in background?” / “백그라운드로 실행할까요?”
- “저장할까요?”

Just do it (unless they explicitly say **don’t commit** / **don’t push**).

## Auto-save

- Workspace: `.vscode/settings.json` → `files.autoSave: afterDelay` (1s), `formatOnSave`.
- Agent: use Write/StrReplace so files are saved; do not leave edits only in chat.

## After every implementation (code, i18n, config)

Not for question-only replies.

1. `git status` and `git diff --stat`
2. **Commit** on `main` (clear message; no secrets)
3. **Push** `origin main`
4. **Deploy verify** (background — see below) until **Deploy Web** succeeds or report failure + fix
5. Reply with: commit hash, deploy status, live URL  
   `https://zeus223308-art.github.io/study-focus-app/`

Skip commit/push only when: user said not to, no file changes, or exploratory/undecided work.

Never: `.env`, keys, `git config`, force-push.

## Background shell (always automatic)

Run long commands in **background** without asking:

| Task | Example |
|------|---------|
| Deploy wait | `gh run watch <id> --exit-status` or poll `gh run list` |
| Dev server | `npx expo start` |
| Install / export | `npm ci`, `npx expo export --platform web` |
| Typecheck | `npx tsc --noEmit` when it may exceed ~30s |

Use `block_until_ms: 0` or background + `Await` / read terminal output. Report result when done.

## Cross-platform reminder

Same bundle for **iOS/Android mobile browsers** and desktop web (GitHub Pages). UI: `useViewportLayout`, safe area, modals **outside** `ScrollView` — see `responsive-ui.mdc`.
